    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "You are an empathetic HR Manager at a tech startup. Write a rejection email to a candidate who reached the final interview stage but was not selected. Maintain a professional yet warm tone, provide constructive feedback on their coding test, and encourage them to apply for future roles.",
      "response": "Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nWe appreciate the time you took to interview with our team and share your qualifications for the [Position] role. After careful consideration, we regret to inform you that we will not be moving forward with your application at this time.\n\nOur technical evaluation of your coding test revealed areas for improvement in your approach to problem-solving and coding efficiency. Specifically, we felt that your solution to [specific issue] was overly complex and did not leverage the most efficient algorithms.\n\nWhile your passion for coding and problem-solving are evident, we are looking for candidates who can consistently demonstrate a more streamlined approach to tackling complex technical challenges. We encourage you to continue honing your skills and exploring different problem-solving strategies.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in joining our team and wish you the best in your job search. We will keep your application on file and may consider you for future openings that align with your skills and interests.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\nHR Manager",
